Opportunity is waiting for you at Cal State Monterey Bay!

There has never been a more exciting time to be a Cal State Monterey Bay student! We are a university focused on making an impact and hope you are ready to join us to do the same. The university currently offers a total of 24 undergraduate degrees with over 30 included concentrations, more than 30 minors, seven graduate degrees, and several teacher certification options.

Everything you need to know about Admissions is available on our website. Should you have more in-depth questions, we encourage you to email, call, or drop by the Office of Admissions - our expert staff is here to help!

ASR and FSR Notices of Availability
Pursuant to the Jeanne Clery Disclosure of Campus Security Policy and Campus Crime Statistics Act, the 2019 Annual Security Report (ASR) is now available for viewing at

. The ASR contains the current security and safety-related policy statements, emergency preparedness and evacuation information, crime prevention and sexual assault prevention information, and drug and alcohol prevention programming. The ASR also contains statistics of Clery Act crimes for CSU Monterey Bay for 2016, 2017, and 2018. A paper copy of the ASR is available upon request by contacting the Office of the Clery Officer located at
, B101, by sending an e-mail to clerycompliance@csumb.edu, or by calling (831) 582-3154.
The Annual Fire Safety Report (FSR) is also available through Student Housing & Residential Life (SHRL) and is available for viewing at

. The report contains information regarding fire safety, how to report a fire, community response to a fire incident, and fire statistics for on-campus student residential facilities for 2016, 2017, and 2018. If you would like to receive hard copies of this information, you can stop by the SHRL front desk in the
, send an e-mail to student_housing@csumb.edu, or call (831) 582-3378.

Take a tour from the comfort of your home. "Download" the Cal State Monterey PocketSights tour app today.
